General:
For sale is a brand new Benelli M4 with authentic M4 collapsible skeletonized stock.  This shotgun needs no introduction and I think most will agree that this is one of the most sought-after firearms in the world, and in its most desired configuration.  I really, REALLY did not want to sell this but my financial situation has left me no choice.

This gun is in perfect condition both functionally and cosmetically and has only been test fired twice: once by Benelli and once by myself (5 rounds) just to function test after making it 922r compliant; otherwise it was literally a safe KING and bragging rights piece.  Take a look at the picture below to see the spotless chamber.

----------
Price:
I feel my asking price is fair considering the research and work required to make this M4 922r compliant and legal to own in any configuration in CA...not to mention the overpriced $400 stock.  I've spent many hours searching forums and websites to learn the legal complexities of this gun as well as the gunsmithing that's required for the conversion, so if anything the price factors in time, labor, and legal knowledge too.  I'm willing to take trade-ins from the list below and offers for how much you want for them:

Glocks any model, Gen 3 or 4
Walther PPK, any caliber
S&W Models 10, 15, or 36
Remington 700, any RH version in .308
Steyr Scout in .308
IMI Desert Eagle, various models
IMI Tavor in FDE
AK-74s, various models
HK pistols, various models

----------
922r Compliance:
There are complex legal issues with this gun due to it's import nature and fame, 922r compliance being the most important to understand.  For a more detailed explanation about this law please check out these sites:

http://freedomfightertactical.com/922r-faq/
http://www.tapco.com/section922r/

For the conversion I've acquired and installed these 3 acceptable parts:
Hammer - http://geissele.com/benelli-m4-super-90-hammer.html
Magazine body - http://davesmetalworks.com/m4.html
Magazine follower - http://nordiccomp.com/retail/shop/followers/nc-low-drag-follower-12-ga/

I'll be more than happy to teach interested buyers about all the legalities of this gun, especially the laws regarding the collapsible stock, but in summary this gun is now 100% legal to own in CA with either stock (traditional or skeletonized) and either magazine capacity (standard or extended).

----------
Terms:
You'll have to provide a phone number that I can reach you at and preferred calling time if you have one. I'll also be calling from my personal cell phone.  I won't deal with anyone who's not willing to speak over the phone first.

Face-to-Face Transfer -
1. I live in Chino, CA and require any interested buyers to meet at the Turner Outdoorsman in Chino Hills. I've conducted many private-party gun transfers there before and know that it's a great and safe location to meet and conduct PPTs at.
2. You are responsible for all the private party transfer fees.
3. I prefer cash but given the high price of this item I will also take Paypal if you trust me enough.  With Paypal you would have to pay me IN FULL AND IN ADVANCE before meeting though, but at least you have that buyer protection Paypal offers.

Shipping to FFL -
1. I can have this shipped from my FFL dealer to yours.  I will need to verify who your dealer is and it will help if he/she works for a business I can easily look up online or call.
2.  You'll have to send a copy of your FFL dealer's license to both me and my FFL dealer.  I can discuss those details over phone though and I won't deal with anyone who is not willing to chat over the phone first.  I'm also aware of the possible scams people run on sites like these so don't even try.

I apologize for the strict terms but I've bought and sold enough guns online to know what people are capable of and just want to protect myself and any potential buyers.  Otherwise I consider myself a nice and trustworthy individual and only want to deal with others who are the same. 

----------

The second is a yet unidentified Lee Enfield, chambered in .303 British, and apparently made in India. There is some light surface rust on the front sight, but otherwise it's in excellent shape. I am researching exactly what type of Enfield this is, but it's proving more difficult than I'd hoped.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Black Mathews ZXT LOADED with SKB TSA approved case
location: picayune, Kiln, Bay St. Louis, Nicholson, Gulfport / Biloxi, Mississippi
postcontent:
I purchased this bow new and had it set up last fall in September from the Mathews dealer that I have always used (my 3rd Mathews) in Virgiinia.  I have loved all of my Mathews, but this one is the smoothest, fastest (320+ FPS), and most forgiving of them all!  You will not find a quieter bow that will shoot a cleaner paper than this bow!  
After about 3 weeks I hurt my shoulder at work and still can not shoot it.  There is absolutely NOTHING wrong with the bow (if there is as much as a tiny scratch, I'm unaware of it).  I shot it probably 150 or so times before I got hurt.  There are too many things to list, if I miss something, please email with questions, I will gladly answer them. The pictures will tell you more about the bow that I can, but I will do my best.  I have and can take more pictures if needed.   
Black Mathews ZXT was in the shop from factory with 60lb-70lb (currently around 65ish) and a 28" draw.  Being the only black one, I had them put a 29" cam on it for my draw length.  It comes with everything in the pics which includes (but not limited to): 
QAD Ultra-Rest HD Pro Series drop away rest 
Trophy Ridge Micro Cypher 7 pin lighted fiber sight 
Mathews dampened quick detach Arrow Web T-Series Quiver 
12 Bone Collector arrows (I'm not sure, but I believe there may be 1 that is from my older bow mixed in accidentally) with 100g practice tips 6 G5 T3 broad heads (never shot except a couple with practice blades into "The Block")
Tru-Fire Hardcore Buckle fold back release 
There are a few red Tracer Knocks, some the batteries have died in, there is a new pack of 3 batteries included 
SKB ATA Single Parallel Limb Bow Case (at the time, and as far as I know, they still do not make a hard side TSA approved case specifically for this bow.  There are some that advertise for z7, z9 and zxt, but you have to cut the water jet foam for the ZXT to fit without forcing the cams.  That in turn voids the content protection from SKB) 
After only a few shots, I had found the feel of the bow and was consistently cloverleaf grouping at 30 yards.  The peep is perfectly matched for sight picture for one or two eye open shooting with the Trophy Ridge sight.  
Before you think I'm nuts with my price, understand the case alone was $300.  You can check current prices of the equipment, but here is my rough cost; Bare bow $799, QAD rest $200, Trophy Ridge sight $200, Mathews quiver $100+, release $100, arrows $115, broad heads $65, Tracer Knocks $70.  I know that this bow is considered used but is as close to new as one will ever be. I don't expect to recoup near the full amount, I'm selling it for about 1/2 of what it would cost to buy the same new. 
I do not see any relief in the near future for my shoulder, so I am selling this to free up some invested money for bills.
** I will NOT part it out.  I have no use for the case without the bow and will have no way of protecting the bow without the case.  I'm selling it cheap enough to sacrifice it all!**
